		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Edward Abbey</span></strong> was an American author and essayist known for his advocacy of environmental issues and criticism of public-land policies. Born in Pennsylvania, he made the American West his home from the time he was seventeen. He wrote more than twenty books of fiction and nonfiction before he died in 1989.</p><a href="/contributors/edward-abbey" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
